This approach creates **dangling links** if the owner deletes the file while other users still have active links, as the node (and its disk blocks) may be freed prematurely. The link count ensures proper cleanup only when the last link is removed, but if the owner deletes it without decrementing the count (or if the system fails to track it), shared users lose access. This is a classic issue in Unix-like systems with hard links.
